00:19:00.478 --> 00:19:01.834
MATT: Oh, man.

00:19:01.834 --> 00:19:03.699
IKO: Yeah, right?

00:19:03.699 --> 00:19:05.746
MATT: You're making me choose.

00:19:05.746 --> 00:19:07.597
IKO: You asked us to!

00:19:07.597 --> 00:19:18.489
MATT: Because I-- I'm like-- I got my Final Fantasy
VI here, and I got my Chrono Trigger here, and I

00:19:18.489 --> 00:19:25.726
got my Suikoden I and II here. Ah, why are you
doing this to me? I'll have-- okay, no, I'll go

00:19:25.726 --> 00:19:30.485
with probably Final Fantasy VI overall.

00:19:30.485 --> 00:19:34.240
(cheering)

00:19:34.240 --> 00:19:37.637
MATT: Partly because, one, when it came out it was
seriously pushing the limits of what we had seen

00:19:37.637 --> 00:19:43.329
capable of the SNES, especially once you got your
first airship moment in-game, you're like, "What?!

00:19:43.389 --> 00:19:52.146
"It's a 3D round world!" But the story was so rich,
the characters were so deep, and the story

00:19:52.146 --> 00:19:59.663
respected you enough to go into some interesting,
dark adult themes that dealt with elements of loss of one's

00:19:59.702 --> 00:20:06.436
family, of suicide-- going into a lot of really
interesting, dark places that these tiny little

00:20:06.436 --> 00:20:11.983
16-bit characters that are maybe a collection of
40 pixels still make you cry in your room, going

00:20:11.983 --> 00:20:17.765
like, "No, Celes, don't do it! You just need to
find healthier fish to feed to Cid until he gets

00:20:17.765 --> 00:20:26.927
"better." That's a real part of the game. It was an
incredible story, such a wonderfully thought-out

00:20:26.927 --> 00:20:36.413
world, and then you had a wendigo in your party,
and Gogo, whatever the hell he was. It was such a

00:20:36.413 --> 00:20:42.858
good game, and you had the loss of Captain Leo. It
was a dark RPG compared to previous ones, so I

00:20:42.858 --> 00:20:49.425
loved that one and it affected me profoundly when
it came out. So I'd say, in the ways it helped me

00:20:49.425 --> 00:20:59.417
run a game, it tremendously helped me understand
that there is a lot of enjoyment in the difficulty

00:20:59.417 --> 00:21:03.767
of adversity and overcoming it. And it also
allowed me to understand that sometimes it's okay

00:21:03.767 --> 00:21:09.107
to have a villain that's just pure evil. I love
myself villains you can understand-- Sephiroth,

00:21:09.107 --> 00:21:14.775
