01:17:10.930 --> 01:17:25.042
TRUSTIN: So. I have two questions. First one is
just: I'm trying to make this character that's a

01:17:25.042 --> 01:17:36.207
super destruction-happy, fun-fun, kill-kill type of
character, very much based off of Jinx or Harley Quinn.

01:17:36.207 --> 01:17:37.176
MATT: Okay, yeah, yeah.

01:17:37.176 --> 01:17:46.028
TRUSTIN: Just take some joy in causing as much
panic and fear and stuff. I was wondering what

01:17:46.028 --> 01:17:48.984
sort of class you might recommend for that?

01:17:48.984 --> 01:17:56.713
MATT: Oh, man. Well, talk to your group. Make sure
that they know the kind of character you're making

01:17:56.713 --> 01:18:01.817
so that you don't end up bringing that to the
table with a lawful good paladin. Because that

01:18:01.817 --> 01:18:04.681
might be a very short campaign, for you or them.

01:18:04.681 --> 01:18:06.820
TRUSTIN: I don't know, I feel like it could be
fun.

01:18:06.820 --> 01:18:12.523
MATT: It could be interesting. Just be aware, it
might be a very short, fun campaign. But if you're

01:18:12.523 --> 01:18:18.270
all playing sort of a Suicide Squad-type,
whatever-it-takes-to-get-the-job-done group, then

01:18:18.270 --> 01:18:26.370
it can be a lot of fun and rampant destruction.
And in that case, I mean, barbarian, man. You're

01:18:26.370 --> 01:18:32.844
just an engine of up-front destruction. Yes!
(laughs) It's a class designed to be like,

01:18:32.844 --> 01:18:36.928
"Oh, that? I want to kill it. I want to kill it in
the face with my face."

01:18:36.928 --> 01:18:39.496
(laughter)

01:18:39.496 --> 01:18:42.772
MATT: So barbarian's great, but then you get
multiclass into some other elements, like

01:18:42.772 --> 01:18:46.126
barbarian with some fighter classes for action
surge, as you've seen with Grog, is disgusting.

01:18:46.126 --> 01:18:54.076
Barbarian-- or if you like to tear things together
as a beast, you can take druid with a couple

01:18:54.076 --> 01:18:57.229
levels of barbarian, so you can rage and then
beast shape.

01:18:57.229 --> 01:18:59.703
(cheering)

01:18:59.703 --> 01:19:04.202
MATT: So you're like, "Oh, I'm sorry, you think
this creature's scary, this giant sabretoothed

01:19:04.202 --> 01:19:06.177
cat? How about if it takes half damage?"

01:19:06.177 --> 01:19:08.386
(laughter)

01:19:08.386 --> 01:19:14.995
MATT: But if you want-- I mean, then you also have
wizard if you want to just tear things apart, or

01:19:14.995 --> 01:19:19.632
warlock's fun, too. Warlock's a great option if
you want to be more like crazy orchestrator of

01:19:19.632 --> 01:19:26.481
death to everything around you. "And you're dead!
Hahaha! And your house is on fire! And I summon a

01:19:26.481 --> 01:19:33.307
demon beast to devour your family! (cackles)" Also
fun. So for what you're describing, I think good

01:19:33.307 --> 01:19:35.711
fits would be barbarian or warlock as a base, most
definitely.

