01:24:33.239 --> 01:24:38.743
ALEXIS: I actually had a friend want me to ask you
a question, so I'm doing that for him. He wanted to

01:24:38.743 --> 01:24:44.117
know: what class did you first start out, and did you
start favoring a specific race for making characters?

01:24:44.117 --> 01:24:51.765
MATT: My first character ever was a human wizard
named Trent. Emeritus Trent, which is actually-- I

01:24:51.765 --> 01:24:56.186
took the name from the Xanth book series by Piers
Anthony, and I was like, "I want to be a wizard

01:24:56.186 --> 01:25:01.203
that uses a sword, get up in the fray!" Because I
didn't know what the hell I was doing. So I used a

01:25:01.203 --> 01:25:05.616
militant wizard kit in 2nd Edition, which
basically was the worst wizard kit ever. It

01:25:05.616 --> 01:25:08.499
basically was like, "You get no benefits, except
you can use a sword, so now you're a wizard who

01:25:08.499 --> 01:25:09.681
gets up in front and killed."

01:25:09.681 --> 01:25:11.670
(laughter)

01:25:11.670 --> 01:25:16.651
MATT: Which happened. So yeah, no. That was my
first character. It was really bad. As far as

01:25:16.651 --> 01:25:22.580
races I tend to favor while creating characters,
there's a glut of elves. Don't get me wrong, I

01:25:22.580 --> 01:25:26.390
like myself some elves, but everyone's like, "I
want to be an elf!" I want to be a dwarf. I love

01:25:26.390 --> 01:25:30.269
dwarves. Dwarves and halflings get
underrepresented, I believe. So those are my two

01:25:30.269 --> 01:25:33.682
favorite races and probably the two that I'd play
if I got to create another character. Definitely.

01:25:33.682 --> 01:25:34.848
AUDIENCE MEMBER: I'm a halfling rogue!

01:25:34.848 --> 01:25:37.805
MATT: Yeah! Represent! Halfling!

