01:26:55.283 --> 01:26:57.846
that is big and has followers?"

01:26:57.846 --> 01:27:04.972
MATT: I think when we began to get mass donations
to charity, to 826LA, when we began to get $100

01:27:04.972 --> 01:27:10.185
donations, $200 donations, I was like, people are
legitimately excited about supporting these

01:27:10.185 --> 01:27:13.886
charitable causes in the name of playing
roleplaying games. It was amazing. And then people

01:27:13.886 --> 01:27:19.050
were asking us to make merch, make merch. "I don't
know what that is! We'll just make 100 t-shirts

01:27:19.050 --> 01:27:22.521
and see if you want to buy them. Hey, guys! So we
put a couple t-shirts up there if you want to--

01:27:22.521 --> 01:27:23.805
they're sold out? What?"

01:27:23.805 --> 01:27:26.105
(laughter)

01:27:26.105 --> 01:27:30.679
MATT: That was when it really hit home, when we
